== Call by Contract (CbC) ==

A JavaScript library with function argument assertions.
The current version contains these assertions:

* <code>defined</code>
* <code>notNull</code>
* <code>bool</code>
* <code>func</code>
* <code>number</code>
* <code>object</code>
* <code>string</code>
* <code>notEmpty</code>

The interface is fluid and specially optimised for the 
Visual Studio JavaScript IntellIsense.

The library can be installed with
[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuget NuGet].
You can find the package here: http://nuget.org/packages/cbc.
Here is a link to the source code:
https://github.com/knutkj/kkj/blob/master/src/cbc.assert.js.

Here is a simple example of usage:

 function showMessage (message) {
	cbc.assert.that.param("message", message).is
		.defined()
		.and.notNull()
		.and.string()
		.and.notEmpty();
	alert(message);
 }